title: 9News Melbourne | Sunday November 28 | Full Episode
description: Tonight in the 9News Melbourne bulletin, a 35-year-old man is fighting for his life following a violent stabbing near a popular South Yarra nightclub, with an alleged offender now in custody facing a string of charges. In a high-stakes police operation on the Princes Highway, three teenagers were arrested at gunpoint after allegedly using a knife to carjack an elderly man and his passengers in Hampton Park. We also bring you exclusive comments from MCG curator Matt Page, who speaks out for the first time following the controversial two-day Ashes Test that has left Cricket Australia facing a $10 million refund bill. In world news, President Zelenskyy prepares for high-stakes peace talks with Donald Trump at Mar-a-Lago as Kyiv reels from a fresh wave of deadly Russian strikes. Closer to home, the ACCC is urging Australians to switch energy providers as rising household bills hit family budgets, while in Tasmania, Master Lock Comanche has claimed a hard-fought victory in the 80th Sydney to Hobart yacht race. title: 9News Brisbane | Sunday December 28 | Full Episode
description: The Queensland bulletin begins with a developing weather emergency as record-breaking rainfall and severe flood alerts lash North and Northwest Queensland, isolating communities and threatening livestock. We take you live to our weather experts for the latest forecasts and travel to the front lines where emergency services are bracing for further wild weather across the Carpenteria Shire.  Beyond the weather, we cover significant local developments including the successful removal of a damaged crane at Southport and a high-level investigation into the Queensland Police Commissioner. On the national stage, we bring you the thrilling conclusion of the Sydney to Hobart Yacht Race as Comanche claims line honours, alongside the fallout from the controversial two-day Boxing Day Test at the MCG. Finally, our international coverage tracks the escalating conflict in Ukraine as President Zelenskyy prepares for pivotal talks in the United States, as well as the immediate aftermath of a powerful 6.6 magnitude earthquake in Taiwan.
